<% content_for :title, "Search Files Tool" %>
<% content_for :subtitle do %>
    High-performance codebase search using PostgreSQL full-text capabilities
<% end %>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Overview" %>

<p>Langgraph Feature (not Rails): </p>

<p>The <code>SearchFilesTool</code> is a powerful LangChain-compatible tool for searching through codebases using PostgreSQL's advanced full-text search capabilities. It enables AI agents to find relevant code files based on content, file paths, or both, with support for complex boolean queries and parallel execution.</p>

<div class="alert alert-primary">
    <p><strong>Key Capabilities:</strong></p>
    <ul>
        <li>Parallel multi-search execution</li>
        <li>Content and path-based searching</li>
        <li>Three search modes: plain, phrase, and boolean</li>
        <li>PostgreSQL ts_rank relevance scoring</li>
        <li>Efficient database-level filtering</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Architecture" %>

<p>The tool leverages PostgreSQL's powerful text search features:</p>

<pre><code class="language-mermaid">
graph LR
    A[Search Query] --> B[SearchFilesTool]
    B --> C{Search Type}
    C -->|Content| D[Full-Text Search]
    C -->|Path| E[Pattern Matching]
    C -->|Both| F[Combined Search]
    D --> G[PostgreSQL tsvector]
    E --> H[ILIKE Matching]
    F --> I[Ranked Results]
    G --> I
    H --> I
    I --> J[Return Files]
</code></pre>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Search Modes" %>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Plain Search" %>

<p>Default mode that finds all specified words in any order:</p>

<pre><code class="language-typescript">const result = await searchFilesTool.invoke({
    searches: [{
        content: "authentication user login",  // Finds files with all three words
        searchMode: "plain",
        limit: 5
    }]
});

// Matches files containing:
// - "user authentication and login"
// - "login method for user authentication"  
// - "authentication of user during login"</code></pre>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Phrase Search" %>

<p>Finds exact phrases in the specified order:</p>

<pre><code class="language-typescript">const result = await searchFilesTool.invoke({
    searches: [{
        content: "async function handleSubmit",  // Exact phrase
        searchMode: "phrase",
        limit: 5
    }]
});

// Only matches files with exact phrase:
// - "async function handleSubmit(event) {"
// Won't match:
// - "async handleSubmit function"
// - "function async handleSubmit"</code></pre>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Boolean Search" %>

<p>Complex queries with AND (&), OR (|), and NOT (!) operators:</p>

<pre><code class="language-typescript">const result = await searchFilesTool.invoke({
    searches: [{
        content: "(authentication | authorization) & user & !deprecated",
        searchMode: "boolean",
        limit: 10
    }]
});

// Matches files that:
// - Contain "authentication" OR "authorization"
// - AND contain "user"
// - AND do NOT contain "deprecated"</code></pre>

