<%= h3_with_anchor "Tool Description for Agents" %>

<pre><code class="language-text">Search for files in the codebase using PostgreSQL full-text search.
Supports three search modes:
- plain: Finds all words in any order (default)
- phrase: Exact phrase matching
- boolean: Complex queries with &, |, ! operators

Can search by file content, path, or both simultaneously.
Returns files ranked by relevance with their content.</code></pre>

<%= h2_with_anchor "API Reference" %>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Input Schema" %>

<pre><code class="language-typescript">interface SearchFilesInput {
    searches: SearchQuery[]
}

interface SearchQuery {
    content?: string;        // Text to search in file contents
    path?: string;          // Pattern to match in file paths
    searchMode?: "plain" | "phrase" | "boolean";  // Default: "plain"
    limit?: number;         // Max results per query (default: 2)
}</code></pre>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Output Schema" %>

<pre><code class="language-typescript">interface SearchFilesOutput {
    results: SearchResult[];
    totalFiles: number;     // Count of unique files across all searches
}

interface SearchResult {
    query: SearchQuery;     // The original query
    files: FileResult[];
}

interface FileResult {
    path: string;          // File path
    content: string;       // File content (truncated if large)
    rank: number;          // Relevance score (0-1)
}</code></pre>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Database Implementation" %>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Schema Design" %>

<pre><code class="language-sql">-- Code files table with full-text search
CREATE TABLE code_files (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    path TEXT UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    content TEXT,
    content_vector tsvector,              -- Full-text search vector
    language VARCHAR(50),
    size_bytes INTEGER,
    last_modified TIMESTAMP,
    created_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW(),
    updated_at TIMESTAMP DEFAULT NOW()
);

-- Indexes for performance
CREATE INDEX idx_content_vector ON code_files USING GIN(content_vector);
CREATE INDEX idx_file_path ON code_files(path);
CREATE INDEX idx_path_pattern ON code_files(path varchar_pattern_ops);</code></pre>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Search Implementation" %>

<pre><code class="language-sql">-- Plain text search
SELECT path, content,
       ts_rank(content_vector, plainto_tsquery('english', $1)) as rank
FROM code_files
WHERE content_vector @@ plainto_tsquery('english', $1)
ORDER BY rank DESC
LIMIT $2;

-- Phrase search
SELECT path, content,
       ts_rank_cd(content_vector, phraseto_tsquery('english', $1)) as rank
FROM code_files
WHERE content_vector @@ phraseto_tsquery('english', $1)
ORDER BY rank DESC
LIMIT $2;

-- Boolean search with websearch syntax
SELECT path, content,
       ts_rank_cd(content_vector, websearch_to_tsquery('english', $1)) as rank
FROM code_files
WHERE content_vector @@ websearch_to_tsquery('english', $1)
ORDER BY rank DESC
LIMIT $2;</code></pre>

<%= h2_with_anchor "Performance Optimization" %>

<%= h3_with_anchor "Indexing Strategy" %>

<ol>
    <li><strong>GIN Index on tsvector:</strong> Enables fast full-text searches</li>
    <li><strong>B-tree Index on path:</strong> Quick exact path lookups</li>
    <li><strong>Pattern Index on path:</strong> Efficient LIKE/ILIKE queries</li>
    <li><strong>Partial Indexes:</strong> For frequently filtered subsets</li>
</ol>

