<%= h2_with_anchor "Best Practices" %>

<ol>
    <li><strong>Use Appropriate Search Mode:</strong>
        <ul>
            <li>Plain: General searching, multiple terms</li>
            <li>Phrase: Exact code snippets</li>
            <li>Boolean: Complex filtering logic</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li><strong>Combine Path and Content:</strong> Narrow searches by using both parameters</li>
    <li><strong>Batch Related Searches:</strong> Execute multiple searches in one call</li>
    <li><strong>Set Reasonable Limits:</strong> Balance between coverage and performance</li>
    <li><strong>Index Maintenance:</strong> Keep search indexes updated as files change</li>
    <li><strong>Cache Common Queries:</strong> Consider caching frequent search patterns</li>
</ol>

<div class="alert alert-warning">
    <p><strong>Important:</strong> The search quality depends on proper text processing and indexing. Ensure files are properly indexed with appropriate language settings for best results.</p>
</div>

